<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=513&amp;p=4029#p4029</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=513&amp;p=4029#p4029"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Games that use MMC5]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=513&amp;p=4029#p4029"><![CDATA[
One possible reason why Castlevania 3 used the MMC5 is because the VRC6 (used in 悪魔城伝説 a.k.a. akuden a.k.a. CV3j) used a rather odd bank switching layout (16KB bank at 8000-BFFF, 8KB bank at C000-DFFF, last 8KB hardwired at E000-FFFF) which only the MMC5 was capable of reproducing (no other Nintendo mappers have 24KB worth of swappable banks; MMC1, MMC4, and MMC3/MMC6 have only 16KB worth).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Wed Aug 24, 2005 1:34 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
