<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=513&amp;p=4021#p4021</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=513&amp;p=4021#p4021"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Games that use MMC5]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=513&amp;p=4021#p4021"><![CDATA[
The Japanese Castlevania 3, Akumajou Densetsu, was released using Konami's VRC6 MMC, Konami reworked the game to use Nintendo's MMC5. Konami didn't release it on VRC6 here probably because Nintendo encouraged uniformity or it wasn't cost-effective since CV3 wouldn't sell for $80 like it would in Japan. The extra audio channels can only be input to a Famicom due to the audio passing through the Famicom's cart connector. (People have however managed to mix in the audio manually on a NES)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Wed Aug 24, 2005 8:15 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
